msContents.textLang: The primary language in this manuscript is Latin.

div.p:
[Information about cover?]
A fragment of the lower inside quadrant is all that remains of the torn title page.
The first two Masses from pp. [1-85] are missing.

body.p:
SVPERIORVM [PERMISSV]
SALMA[N]T[ICAE]
Ex officina typographica Antonij V[AZQUEZ]
Anno à Christo nato M. DC.

div.p:
Missa Elisabeth Zachariae (4vv)
92 MISSA ELISABETH ZACHARIAE. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRUCEÑA. 93. Kyrie, Gloria, and Credo: missing.
Sanctus ([86]-[89]): Superius and Tenor missing; small losses from Altus and Bassus; Osanna in 3/2.
The upper outside quadrant of pp. 87-88 survives, detatched from the book. Most of the Altus and some of the Bassus is preserved on p. 87 while most of the Superius and some of the Tenor is preserved on p. 88. A small fragment of the outer side of pp. [89]-[90] survives, detatched from the binding. It preserves some notes from the Bassus of the Sanctus and the Tenor of the Benedictus.
Benedictus ([90]-91): 3vv (SAT), Altus complete; Superius missing, significant losses from Tenor.
Agnus (92-3): Superius, Altus, and Tenor complete; Bassus lacks most of final stave.
Source motet: Francisco Guerrero, Elisabeth Zacharaiae (secunda pars: Dominus ab utero) 5vv (SSTTB) from Mottetta (Venice: Filio Antonii Gardani, 1570) [RISM G4871], no. 48 and Motecta (Venice: Giacomo Vincenti, 1597) [RISM G4877], no. 47.

Missa Quae est ista (4vv)
94 MISSA QVE PROGREDITVR. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 95
Kyrie (94-99): Superius, Altus, and Bassus complete; minor losses from Tenor.
Gloria (100-107): Superius complete; minor losses from Altus, Tenor and Bassus.
Credo (108-117): Superius and Altus complete; minor losses from Tenor and Bassus.
Sanctus (118-119): complete.
Benedictus (120-121): 3vv (SAB), complete.
Agnus (122-123): complete.
Source motet: Giovanni Pierluigi da Palestrina, Quae es ista quae progreditur 5vv (SSTTB) from Motettorum quinque vocibus liber quartus (Rome: Alessandro Gardano, 1584) [Tenor and Bassus, 1583; Superius, Altus, and Quintus, 1584] [RISM P716], no. 23.

Missa Tu es pastor ovium (4vv)
124 MISSA TV ES PARTOR [sic] OVIVM. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 125
Kyrie (124-125): Superius and Altus complete; significant losses from Tenor, minor losses from Bassus.
Gloria (126-129): Superius and Altus complete; significant losses from Tenor, minor losses from Bassus.
Credo (130-135): Superius and Altus complete; significant losses from Tenor and Bassus.
Sanctus (136-137): Superius and Altus complete; some losses from Tenor and Bassus.
Benedictus (138-139): 3vv (SAT) complete.
Agnus (140-141): complete.
Source motet: Giovanni Pierluigi da Palestrina, Tu es pastor ovium 4vv (SATB), from Motecta festorum totius anni liber primus (Venice: Antonio Gardano, 1564) [RISM P689], no. 14.

Missa Veni de Libano (4vv)
142 MISSA VENI DE LIBANO. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 143
Kyrie (142-143): Superius, Altus, and Bassus complete; losses from Tenor.
Gloria (144-147): complete.
Credo (148-157): Superius and Altus complete; significant losses from Tenor and Bassus.
Sanctus (158-159): complete.
Benedictus (160-161): 3vv (ATB) complete. SVPERIVS TACET.
Agnus (162-163): 5vv (SSATB) complete.
Veni de Libano: source unidentified.

Magnificat Primi toni (4vv/3vv)
164 PRIMI TONI. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 165
Pages 173-175 missing.
Anima mea (164-165): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Quia respexit (166-167): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Et misericordia (168-169): 3vv (SAT) complet. BASVS REQVIESCIT.
Deposuit (170-171): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Suscepit (172-[173]): 4vv (SATB) Superius and Tenor complete, Altus and Tenor(?) missing.
Gloria patri ([174-175]): missing.

div.p: The ornamented 'Q' is the first word of the hymn, 'Quia.' Each section of the choir in the book begins with the same ornamented letter.
You can comment on text that wasn't transcribed via hotspots.

Magnificat Secundi toni (5vv/4vv/6vv)
[176 SECVNDI TONI. v. vocum.] // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 177
Page 176 missing.
Anima mea ([176]-177): 5vv (SSATB) Superius 1 and Tenor missing; Superius 2, Altus, and Bassus complete.
Quia respexit (178-179): 5vv (SSATB) complete.
Et misericordia (180-181): 4vv (SSAT) complete.
Deposuit (182-183): 5vv (SSATB) complete.
Suscepit (184-185): 5vv (SSATB) complete.
Gloria patri (186-187): 6vv (SSAATB) complete. Superius 1 Canon in unisonus; Tenor sing second tone cantus firmus.

Magnificat Tertii toni (4vv/3vv/6vv?)
188 TERTII TONI. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRUCEÑA. 189
Pages 191-196 missing.
Anima mea (188-189): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Quia respexit (188-189): 4vv (SATB) Superius, Altus, and Tenor complete; minor losses from Bassus.
Et misericordia (190-[191]): 3vv (AAB?) Altus 1 complete; Altus 2 and Bassus (?) missing.
Deposuit ([192-193]): [4vv (SATB)] missing.
Suscepit ([194-195]): [4vv (SATB)] missing.
Gloria patri ([196]-197): 5vv? (SSATB) Superius 1 and Tenor missing; Superius 2 and Altus complete; minor losses from Bassus. Altus: Superius in diateseron (sic).

Magnificat Quarti toni (4vv/3vv)
198 QVARTI TONI. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 199
Anima mea (198-199): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Quia respexit (198-199): 4vv (SATB) Superius, Altus, and Tenor complete; minor losses from Bassus.
Et misericordia (200-201): 3vv (SAT) complete. BASVS TACET.
Deposuit (202-203): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Suscepit (204-205): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Gloria patri (206-207): 4vv (SATB) Superius, Altus, and Bassus complete; losses from Tenor. S and A have 3/2; T and B have 3/2 in error.

Magnificat Quinti toni (4vv/3vv/6vv)
208 QVINTI TONI. iiij. vocum.] // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 209
Anima mea (208-209): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Quia respexit (210-211): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Et misericordia (212-213): 3vv (SAT) complete. BASVS REQVIESCIT.
Deposuit (214-215): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Suscepit (216-217): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Gloria patri (218-219): 6vv (SSAATB) complete. Altus 2: CANON IN DIAPENTE.

Magnificat Sexti toni (4vv/3vv)
220 SEXTI TONI. iiij. vocum.] // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 221
Anima mea (220-221): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Quia respexit (222-221 [recte 223): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Et misericordia (224-225): 3vv (SAT) complete. BASVS TACET.
Deposuit (226-227): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Suscepit (228-227 [recte 229): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Gloria patri (218-219): 4vv (SSAT) complete.

Magnificat Septimi toni (4vv/3vv/6vv)
232 SEPTIMI TONI. iiij. vocum.] // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 233
Anima mea (232-233): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Quia respexit (232-233): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Et misericordia (234-235): 3vv (ATB) complete. SVPERIVS TACET.
Deposuit (236-237): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Suscepit (238-239): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Gloria patri (240-241): 6vv (SSAATB) Superius 1, Superius 2, Altus 1, Altus 2, and Bassus complete. minor losses from Tenor; Altus 1: Resolutio in Septima, Bassus: CANON Altus in Septima.

Magnificat Octavi toni (4vv/3vv/6vv)
242 OCTAVI TONI. iiij. vocum.] // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 243
Anima mea (242-243): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Quia respexit (242-243): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Et misericordia (244-245): 3vv (SAT) complete. BASVS REQVIESCIT.
Deposuit (246-247): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Suscepit (248-249): 4vv (SATB) complete.
Gloria patri (250-251): 6vv (SSAATB) complete. Canon. Tenor. In diapason. Altus. In diapente. Bassus. In duodezima. vj. vocu[m].

Tribulationes cordis mea (6vv)
252 PRO QVACVNQVE NECESSITATE. vj. vocu[m]. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 253
Motet (SSAATB), all voices complete.
TRibulationes cordis mei dilatate sunt, De necessitatibus meis, eripe me Domine vide humilitatem meam & laborem meum, & dimite omnia peccata mea. (Psalm 24: 17-18).

Hoc est praeceptum meum (6vv)
256 COMVNE APOSTOLORVM. vj. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 257
Motet (SSAATB), all voices complete.
HOc est præceptum meum, vt diligatis inuicem sicut dilexi vos. Maiorem charitatem nemo habet, vt animam suam ponat quis pro amicis suis. (John 15: 12-13).

Iste Sanctus (6vv)
260 COMVNE VNIVS MARTIRIS. vj. vocu[m]. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 261
Motet (SSAATB), all voices complete.
ISte sanctus pro lege Dei sui, certauit vsque ad mortem, & à verbis impiorum non timuit fundatus enim erat supra firmam petram. (Antiphon at the magnificat, common of a martyr).

Ave sanctissima Maria (6vv)
264 DE VEATA VIRGINE. vj. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 265
Motet (SSAATB), all voices complete. Words tu singularis set in 3/2. S1 and S2 have 3/2 in error.
AVe sanctissima Maria. Mater Dei, Regina cœli, Porta Paradisi, Domina mundi, tu singularis pura es Virgo tu Concepisti lesum sine peccato, libera me ab omni malo, & ora pro peccatis meis. (Marian devotional antiphon, Breviarum Romanum completissimum [Venice: Lucantonio Giunta, 1522] f. 23v.

Stabat mater (5vv)
270 DE BEATA VIRGINE. vj. [sic] vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 271
Motet (SSATB), all voices complete.
STabat mater dolorosa,
iusta crucem lachrimosa,
dum pendebat Filius.
Cuius animam gemente[m],
Contristantem & dolentem
pertransiuit gladius.
ò quam tristis & aflicta
fuit illa benedicta,
mater vnigeniti. (Sequence extract).

O Ildefonse (4vv)
274 DE BEATO ILLEFONSO. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 275
Motet (SATB), all voices complete.
O Ildefonsæ per te vibit domina mea quæ cœli culmina tenet & præsula colaudato redibat. (Constantinus Caietanus, Sanctorum trium episcoporum religionis... [Rome: Mascardum, 1606], p. 118).

Gaudent in caelis (4vv)
276 COMVNE PLVRIMORVM MARTIRVM. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 277
Motet (SATB), all voices complete.
GAudent in cœlis animæ sanctorum qui Christi vestigia sunt secuti, & quia pro eius amore sanguine[m] suum suderunt. (Antiphon at the magnificat, common of mny martyrs).

Hic vir despicien mundum (4vv)
278 Comune Confessorum non Pontificum. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 279
Motet (SATB), all voices complete.
HIc vir dispiciens mundu[m] & terrena triumphas, diuitia cœlo condidit ore manu. (Antiphon at the magnificat, common of a confessor not a bishop).

O doctor optime (4vv)
280 COMVNE DOCTORVM. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 281
Motet (SATB), all voices complete.
O Doctor optime Ecclessiæ sancte lumen, Beate Hieronyme, diuinæ legis amator depræcare pro nobis filium Dei. (Antiphon at the magnificat, common of doctors of the church).

Assumpsit Jesus Petrum (4vv)
282 In transfiguracione Domini. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 281 [recte 283]
Motet (SSAT), all voices complete.
ASumpsit Iesus Petrum & Iacobum & Ioannem frate[m] eius, eduxit eos in montem excelsum seorsum & transfiguratus est ante eos. (Matthew 17: 1-2a).
The first note in the fourth stave of the Tenor has been corrected by hand to F sharp.

Veni sponsa Christi (4vv)
284 COMVNE VIRGINVUM. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 285
Motet (SATB), all voices complete.
VEni sponsa Christi accipe coronam quam tibi Dominum preparauit in eternum. (Antiphon at the magnificat, common of virgins).

Amavit eum Dominus (4vv)
286 Comune Confessorum Pontificum. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 287
Motet (SATB), all voices complete.
AMauit eum Dominus & ornauit eum, stolam gloriæ induit eum, & ad portas Paradisi coronauit eum. (Antiphon at the magnificat, second vespers, common of a confessor bishop).

Salve regina (5vv)
288 DE BEATA VIRGINE. v. vocu[m]. // DIDACVS DE BRVCEÑA. 289
Marian antiphon (SSATB) alternatim setting.
Vita dulcedo (288-289): 5vv (SSATB) complete.
Ad te suspiramus (290-[293]): 5vv (S[SA]TB) Superius 1, Tenor, and Bassus complete; Superius 2 missing; significant losses from Altus.

Benedicamus Domino [1] (4vv)
Benedicamus Domino ([294-95]): 4vv (SATB) Superius and Altus missing; minor losses from Tenor, some losses from Bassus.
p. 294 (beneath Tenor):
BASVS. Eam in Subdiapason.
SVPERIVS. Basum in duodezima.
ALTVS. Superiu[m] in Subdiapason.
TENOR. Altum in Subdiapason.
p. 295 (beneath Bass):
Quando fuerit hæc.
Omnes he quatuor vozes.
Vt sunt Anotate.

Benedicamus Domino [2] (4vv)
Benedicamus Domino ([296-297]): 4vv (SATB): Superius missing, Tenor complete; Altus and Bassus missing. [Ca]non non venio. Vado Retrorsum & non venio.

[?Benedicamus Domino 3]
?Benedicamus Domino ([289-299]). Missing.
